headline: Payments processor FIS posts higher profit on boost from banking solutions unit
summary: Banking and payments processing firm Fidelity National Information Services on Tuesday posted a higher profit for the ‌fourth quarter on strong demand for its financial products and ‌services, sending the company's shares up 3% before the bell. Consumer spending has largely held ​up despite economic uncertainty, with high earners sustaining discretionary demand while middle and lower income households focus on essentials, supporting steady transaction volumes. Higher spending volumes benefit payments tech providers that charge merchants and banks a ‌fee for processing transactions.
